author: Luke Rosiak
description: A Jimmy Carter-era court order that banned the federal government from using tests to measure job applicants’ skills before hiring them has been terminated, setting the stage to dramatically overhaul the nature of the federal workforce in what could be one of President Donald Trump’s most lasting achievements.
title: For The First Time In 40 Years, The Federal Government Can Judge Applicants By Merit
